 Surveys â€“ If you contact Customer Service or participate in one of our promotions, sweepstakes or user surveys, we may ask for additional information, such as your age, interests or product preferences.Â  This information will never be shared with third parties.\r\n\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â â€œEmail to a Friendâ€ â€“ You may be able to share certain content from this website with your friends. In order to do so, we may ask for information such as your name and email address and your friendâ€™s name and email address. When you choose to share content with a friend, we do not store any names or email addresses unless you, or your friend, choose to be added to our TIDE &amp; POOL Swim Club email list. We will not include any other advertisements within the message sent to your friends.\r\n\r\n\r\nNON-PERSONALLY IDENTIFIABLE INFORMATION\r\n\r\nCookies\r\nSeveral of our functions may use cookies. A cookie is a small piece of information sent by a website that is saved on your hard drive by your computerâ€™s browser. Cookies help us remember you when you return to our website.Â  Cookies also hold information a site may need to personalize/enhance your experience and to gather website statistical data, such as which pages are visited, what is included in your shopping cart, the internet providerâ€™s domain name and the addresses of the sites visited immediately before coming to and immediately after leaving tideandpool.com. However, none of this information is associated with you as an individual.Â  It is measured anonymously and only in the aggregate. The information in the cookies lets us trace your â€˜clickstreamâ€™ activity (i.e. the paths taken by visitors to our site and as they move from page to page).Â  This enables us to better serve our customers by revealing which portions of our site are most popular. Cookies contain absolutely no Personal Information. You may disable cookies on your browser. Please review your browserâ€™s instructions for doing so.\r\n\r\nAnalytical Tools\r\nWe may also use various analytical tools in connection with the website to collect information about your visit, including the pages you view, the features you use, the links you click, and other actions you take in connection with the website. This information may include your computer''s Internet protocol (IP) address, your browser type, your operating system, date and time information, and other technical information about your computer. We may also track certain information about the identity of the web site you visited immediately before coming to the website. This information is collected anonymously, and none of this information is identified with you as an individual or contains any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n\r\nUSE OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\nWe use the information we collect for various purposes, including:\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To complete your purchase transactions upon your request\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To provide the services you request\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To keep you informed about the status of your orders\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To identify your product and service preferences, so we can notify you of new or additional products, services and promotions that might be of interest to you\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To notify you of product recalls or provide other information concerning products you have purchased\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To improve our merchandise selections, customer service and overall shopping experience\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To communicate with you by email, postal mail, telephone or other means\r\nâ€¢Â Â  Â To comply with our legal obligations, policies and procedures and for internal administrative and analytical purposes\r\n\r\n\r\nOTHERS WITH WHOM WE MAY SHARE YOUR INFORMATION\r\nService Providers: We may also disclose information to outside companies that help us provide the products and services we offer. For example, we may work with an outside company to: (a) manage a database of customer information (b) assist us in distributing emails (c) assist us with direct marketing and data collection (d) provide us with data storage and analysis (e) provide fraud prevention or (f) engage in other services designed to assist us in maximizing our business potential.Â  We require that these outside companies agree to keep confidential all information we share with them and to use the information only to perform their obligations in the agreements.\r\n\r\nCompliance with Law: We may provide access to your personal information when legally required to do so, to cooperate with police investigations or other legal proceedings, to protect against misuse or unauthorized use of our website, to limit our legal liability and protect our rights, and to protect the rights, property or safety of visitors to this website and the public.\r\n\r\nLINKS TO OTHER SITES\r\nWhile visiting our website, you may link to sites operated by our business partners or other third parties. This does not mean that we endorse these sites or the goods/services advertised or offered on those sites. We do not make any representations or warranties about any website you may access through tideandpool.com.Â  They are independent from us, and we have no control over, or responsibility for, their information or activities.\r\n\r\nIn addition, our privacy practices may differ from those of these other sites. If you provide personal information at one of those sites, you are subject to the privacy policy of the operator of that site, not the TIDE &amp; POOL Privacy Policy. Please make sure you understand the other siteâ€™s privacy policy before providing personal information.\r\n\r\n\r\nYOUR SECURITY\r\nTIDE &amp; POOL goes to great lengths to keep your financial information private and safe.Â  We take appropriate physical, electronic and administrative steps to maintain the security and accuracy of personally identifiable information we collect, including limiting the number of people who have physical access to our database servers, as well as employing electronic security systems and pass